I need to identify the net profit value and decompose it into 5 component sub-items from the income statement.

Looking at the income statement:
- The "Net Profit" line item shows a value of 905750.76 for 2024-02-05
- This represents the amount of profit the entity retains after all expenses

To decompose this into 5 sub-items, I need to identify the main components that contribute to this final net profit figure:

1. Total Revenue: 2869560.42
2. Cost of Goods Sold: 1249000.00
3. Total Expenses: 585907.44
4. Interest Income: 14575.80
5. Tax Expense: 143478.02

The calculation flows as:
- Revenue (2869560.42) - Cost of Goods Sold (1249000.00) = Gross Profit (1620560.42)
- Gross Profit (1620560.42) - Total Expenses (585907.44) + Interest Income (14575.80) = Profit Before Tax (1049228.78)
- Profit Before Tax (1049228.78) - Tax Expense (143478.02) = Net Profit (905750.76)
